    "Here, y t is the 2 × 1 point-at-target vector, ŷt is the cursor's predicted velocity vector at timestep t, D is the 2 × 2 decoder matrix, and ǫ t is the 2 × 1 vector of gaussian noise at timestep t.",
    "We computed the functional SNR (fSNR) as:",
